br>
<br>
My Rallos newbie, Nidal, started getting a lot of trash talk from a red-to-me mage in Steamfont.  It annoyed me, because I'd helped the guy move some stuff between characters (a few plat and a backpack for his brand new necro).  But he was being very foul mouthed, very abusive, and then he started attacking me at every opportunity.<br>
<br>
Revenge is a dish best served cold.  I ignored the guy, hid from him, and concentrated on leveling.  Ended up going to Kaladim to turn in bone chips.  DING!  Level 8.<br>
<br>
Walking home.  Zone into Steamfont.  Sneak/hide by reflex, /who to look for enemies.  See some familiar unpleasant names, sneak/hide around the corner to make sure they aren't hunting right there by the lfay zone.<br>
<br>
And what to my wondering eye should appear but my nemesis, chasing a tiny reindeer.  Actually he was chasing a twink in full bronze.  They hit the zone, but not before I do a con on my guy.  Blue, fancy that!<br>
<br>
I zone a bit behind them.  My new faster computer and cable modem gives me very fast zones, which means they are just going around the corner as I appear.  I target my guy and give chase.<br>
<br>
His victim is boogying for the gfay zone, bagging as he goes.  I run up behind my guy, hit my default hotkey for these situations.  &quot;Hello.  My name is Nidal.  You once tried to kill me.  Prepare to die.&quot;  (Sorry, Inigo, it's just too good not to steal.)  Start attacking.<br>
<br>
Wham wham wham.  He starts whining.  He must be out of mana (or maybe he's not the mage he said he was) because he keeps trying to run out to range and use a big-arse bow on me. I keep closing and thumping.  He's down to less than two bubbles by now.  His first victim (also below half) is now fully bagged and has returned to join the whuppin' party.<br>
<br>
He begins to flee, and I give chase.  He's down to a bubble.  I've lost less than a bubble.  Suddenly (drat!) I'm being whaled on by a Monarch Fae Drake.  I lose another bubble in about two hits, so I boogie for the nearby Steamfont Zone.<br>
<br>
Zone.  Sneak/hide.  Turn around to face the zone.  I don't expect him to come back through right away, but who knows?  Sit to recoup hit points.<br>
<br>
A few minutes later, as I am at full hit points and thinking about moving on, the twink comes through the zone naked (still bagged I assume) at about half health.  A little bit later, my guy zones at full health, and instantly starts chasing the naked twink down the path.  I unhide, give chase, and come up on my guy around the corner.  The twink is in sad shape by the time I get there, but I start with the wham wham wham again.  Somebody I've never seen suddenly starts casting on my guy also.  He starts whining (&quot;No fair!&quot;) and I observe that he seems to have made a lot of enemies.  He's visibly bagging as we take him out.  I get the kill, but the twink ninja loots him.  Twink says he was fully bagged, but I doubt it.<br>
<br>
Funny thing is, he spent the next two hours trash talking the twink and his caster friend in /ooc, but he never mentioned my name.  Suits me just fine.  :-)  The big thing I hate about Rallos is all the unimaginative trash talk.  Articulate invective is fun, but &quot;I ownz U biatch U suk p3nis&quot; gets old real quick. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub2.ezboard.com/ujaisrassiter.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Jais Rassiter</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(8/22/00 11:46:56 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://hoels76.tripod.com/general2.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Revenge is Sweet</span><hr size=1> rofl nicely done <p><P><left>Jais<i>"Roach</i>"Rassiter 34<small>th</small> <cr> Rebel ring Warden of Rodcet Nife,proud memeber of <b>Thy Brethren</b>Apprentice of Glip the pantless Gnome 


